article.headline: Stanford 103, Oregon St. 101
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- Chasson Randle's layup with 37 seconds left in the fourth overtime provided the winning points Saturday in Stanford's 103-101 win against Oregon State. Randle had a game-high 24 points for Stanford (13-3, 3-1), which avoided a conference road sweep after losing two days earlier at Oregon. An off-balance 3-pointer by Oregon State's Roberto Nelson that would have won the game was off the mark. Nelson and Jared Cunningham had 19 points apiece for Oregon State (11-5, 1-3). Stanford, which played its longest game in program history, led 100-95 after Randle scored the first five points of the fourth overtime. The Cardinal didn't give up the lead again.
